  "text": "International business studies have discussed and typically found positive effects of normative integration Nohria 1989), social control (O'Donnell 2000) , and boundary spanning interpersonal interaction [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The common mechanisms driving these issues are personal meetings and the facilitation of human interaction that enables two-way communication as opposed to formal and more detached mechanisms [CITATION_4] leading to knowledge sharing [CITATION_5] .",
